# FastAPI Backend

## Layout

```
backend/app/
├── main.py
├── config.py
├── routers/
├── services/
├── models/
└── schemas/    # Pydantic v2
```

Adjust if the project uses a different backend directory.

## Endpoints

- Async for I/O-bound work; sync only when justified.
- Every route has a response model, tags, and OpenAPI documentation.

## Domain logic

Business rules belong in `services/`, not routers. Domain-specific state machines and terminology live in **project rules**, not shared backend rules.

## Auth

Structure for JWT/session hooks but do not implement auth until requested.

## CORS

Configure allowed origins from environment settings. Include Firebase Hosting URLs, custom domains, and `capacitor://` schemes when native apps are planned.

```python
# ✅ Configure origins from env, not hardcoded in production
origins = settings.cors_origins
```

Adjust path globs if the backend directory differs (e.g. `api/**/*.py`).
